cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on improving the performance of deep learning models for image super-resolution while keeping them fast and lightweight, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial learning (cs.AI) and multi-scale discriminators (cs.MM) to improve the performance of the proposed model. Finally, the paper presents extensive experiments and benchmarks to verify the effectiveness of the proposed model, which is a common practice in neural networks (cs.NE).
